# App version and commit messages

## Single source of truth

The shipped app version lives in **one place**:

- `index.html` → `<meta name="mf-app-version" content="X.Y.Z">`

`package.json` `"version"` must match that meta tag (no leading `v`).

Runtime code reads the meta tag via `MF_APP_VERSION`; do not hardcode version strings elsewhere.

## When to bump

Bump the patch version (`2.9.37` → `2.9.38`) for user-facing releases: copy, SEO, UI, or behavior changes users will see on the live site.

Skip a version bump only for internal/tooling-only changes (e.g. Tailwind build config with no HTML change).

## Commit subject format

When creating a git commit for a versioned release:

1. Read current `mf-app-version` from `index.html` (or bump it first if this release needs a new version).
2. Start the subject with **`vX.Y.Z:`** matching the meta tag (e.g. `v2.9.38: fix landing copy.`).
3. Stage `index.html` (and `package.json` if you bumped version there too) so the diff shows the version change.

Do not guess the version from prior commits, chat history, or the `MF_APP_VERSION` JS fallback.

## Cursor "Generate commit message"

If using the sparkle button, bump and stage `mf-app-version` before generating, then verify the subject matches the meta tag and edit if not.
